# Swift conventions

- Target **macOS 13+**. Use APIs available without bumping deployment unless requested.
- Put reusable types/services in **`MasterFabricCore`**. `mf` and `MasterFabricMenuBar` should call Core, not reimplement IOKit/SMC.
- Prefer small focused types (`*Service`, `*Store`, clear model structs). Avoid mega-files unless extending an existing one (e.g. menubar `App.swift`).
- Public CLI/MCP surface: keep JSON shapes stable; additive changes preferred over breaking renames.
- Formatting: match surrounding file style; no drive-by reformats of unrelated code.
- After changing user-facing version strings, ensure `VERSION` + `make version-sync` stay aligned.

```swift
// ✅ Shared metric in Core
let battery = BatteryService.current()

// ❌ Copy-paste SMC reads into MenuBar App.swift
```
